Program: Outlook
Title: The Woman Who Forgave Her Rapist
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p01452h0
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 14 Feb 2013
Satta Joe was raped during a rebel attack on her village in Sierra Leone. As part of a project to help the country recover from the civil war, Satta agreed to forgive her attacker and take part in a dance of reconciliation. Also, Dr Ahmad Sarmast is an Afghan trumpeter who started a music school in Kabul - now his students are on a tour of the US. And Jackson Gutierrez, the Venezuelan barber from Caracas who has made a movie based on his experiences in the slum district of Caracas. Picture: Outlook presenter Matthew Bannister Show less